{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"content_hash":"ffb0cd56c68c6ceba5c3e92f591cfe1df757b410b2d6f45ee038c5a553141061","digest":{"component_or_area":"plan-review gate Pass-4 coach path","key_entities":["triage_advisories","APPLY_NOW_MARGIN","passes.py","workflow_ops.py","plan_review_coach","verdict[\"triage\"]","block_threshold","priority","DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD","MOVE_REGISTRY","MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA","review_kernel/coach.py","review_kernel/decide.py","orchestrator.py","partition_findings","criteria_routing.json","plan_review_verdict","REVIEW_RESULT","sidecar.build_payload","gate_dispatch.py","_OUTPUT_SCHEMA","validate_structured","tests/unit/test_plan_review_triage.py","docs/plan-review-gate.md"],"problem_keywords":["advisory triage","advisory latency","apply-now vs defer","deterministic ranking","coaching move","surviving advisories","priority bucketing","byte-identical output","no eval gate"],"propositions":["Authors defer advisories because nothing ranks which surviving advisories to apply now versus defer, causing advisory-application latency (caught-but-ignored findings).","Add a deterministic advisory-triage stage to the Pass-4 coach path that partitions surviving advisory findings into apply-now and defer buckets using only fields already on decided findings, with no LLM call and no free prose.","Bucketing rule: an advisory is apply-now iff priority >= block_threshold - APPLY_NOW_MARGIN (default 0.10), else defer; block_threshold defaults to DEFAULT_BLOCK_THRESHOLD (0.95) when absent on DET-tier advisories.","The triage array is sorted deterministically by priority DESC, then criteria[0] ASC (empty criteria sorts last via sentinel '~'), then id ASC, yielding byte-identical output.","Only decision == 'advisory' findings are triaged; blocking findings are excluded and every surviving advisory appears exactly once.","Triage is attached as top-level verdict['triage'] (returned, not persisted); sidecar.build_payload and the kernel coach mechanism stay unchanged, validated post-ship by R7 dogfood latency metric."]},"digest_hash_version":1,"model":"claude-opus-4-8","schema":"ticket_digest_v1"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"TICKET_DIGEST","timestamp":1784259721358445001,"uuid":"38394c07-9c17-4d86-80b3-d5f5621cbb3c"}